Listen, Patty. I hope you understand,
but I am here to support Brick.

33:36.389 --> 33:38.600
I don't want him to think
I'm here to talk to you, so.

33:38.683 --> 33:40.810
Yeah, sure. I get it.

33:49.569 --> 33:52.072
- Patty's totally looking.
- Brick's not.

33:53.156 --> 33:55.408
So. Do you wanna stop?

33:55.492 --> 33:56.618
Actually...

33:57.786 --> 33:58.620
no.

34:01.706 --> 34:02.749
This one's for you, babe.

34:08.420 --> 34:10.047
Hey. I didn't know you were coming.

34:10.130 --> 34:12.676
Your mom said you'd be here.
I wanted to talk to you.

34:12.759 --> 34:15.262
A weird thing happened to me last night
and I feel kind of crazy.

34:15.344 --> 34:17.054
Oh my God, I feel crazy.

34:17.138 --> 34:19.933
I set up Magnolia and Christian
so Magnolia wouldn't be mad about Brick,

34:20.016 --> 34:21.976
but now I can't stop
thinking about Christian.

34:22.060 --> 34:25.438
But I can't steel her boyfriend
a second time, that would be selfish.

34:25.522 --> 34:26.731
Oh my God! Seriously?

34:27.274 --> 34:30.277
Uh! Which hot guy should I be with?
Nobody cares!

34:30.360 --> 34:31.902
Helmet, helmet!

34:35.364 --> 34:36.908
Nonnie, slow down!

34:36.992 --> 34:39.661
Hey, wait! What's wrong?

34:39.744 --> 34:42.956
I told you something crazy happened
to me, but you ran right over it.

34:43.039 --> 34:46.293
- I'm sorry. What happened?
- A girl asked me out.

34:46.585 --> 34:49.337
- What d'you say?
- I didn't really say anything.

34:51.005 --> 34:52.632
Okay, so what's the crazy thing?

34:52.966 --> 34:53.882
That's it!

34:53.967 --> 34:57.304
I just told you. It totally freaks me out.

34:57.387 --> 34:59.222
She said I put out a vibe.

35:03.476 --> 35:05.520
Do you think I put out a vibe?

35:05.604 --> 35:07.772
- A vibe, what kind of vibe?
- A gay vibe!

35:09.107 --> 35:11.318
I don't know,
I've never really thought about it.

35:11.401 --> 35:13.278
Yeah, of course
you've never thought about it.

35:13.361 --> 35:17.032
You've never, ever thought about it,
that's the fucking problem!

35:17.115 --> 35:19.242
- Why are you getting so upset?
- Because!

35:20.201 --> 35:21.202
This!

35:32.589 --> 35:33.590
Nonnie.

35:34.674 --> 35:35.675
I love you.

35:38.303 --> 35:40.138
More than anyone in the world.

35:40.930 --> 35:43.099
But not like that.

35:47.187 --> 35:48.396
Oh, God.

35:49.022 --> 35:50.315
Oh my God.

35:50.398 --> 35:51.858
I've ruined everything.

35:51.941 --> 35:53.985
No. No you didn't.

35:54.069 --> 35:56.029
- Nothing has to change.
- Of course it does.

35:56.112 --> 35:58.365
- Wait.
- Everything's different now.

35:58.448 --> 36:00.408
Why? I don't care.

36:01.743 --> 36:04.829
Oh my God! You always make it about you!

36:04.913 --> 36:06.206
What do you mean, "always"?

36:07.165 --> 36:08.750
Even before you got skinny,

36:08.833 --> 36:13.088
even before Bob and pageants
and the fucking hot guys,

36:13.171 --> 36:15.423
all we ever talked about was you.

36:15.507 --> 36:17.676
How you felt, what you wanted,

36:17.759 --> 36:21.513
and now I'm finally,
finally figuring out what I want

36:21.596 --> 36:23.932
and you're still making it about you?

36:25.433 --> 36:27.769
God! Could you be more self-involved?

36:35.485 --> 36:36.986
Penetrate him!

36:38.363 --> 36:39.739
Penetrate him!

36:39.823 --> 36:41.324
Finish him off!

36:45.954 --> 36:48.790
<i>- Brick Armstrong is down...
- </i> Hold up, son. Easy.

36:49.124 --> 36:50.250
What happened?

36:51.501 --> 36:52.544
I messed up.

36:53.211 --> 36:54.421
Yeah, me too.

36:54.504 --> 36:55.547
Easy.

36:55.839 --> 36:56.965
Are you... Is he all right?

36:57.048 --> 36:58.925
Yeah, it looks like it's just a sprain.

36:59.008 --> 37:01.386
- Oh, thank God.
- Are you kidding me?

37:02.011 --> 37:04.389
This was my biggest meet of the season
and you ruined it.

37:05.682 --> 37:08.393
I like it a lot better
when you didn't care about me, so...

37:09.310 --> 37:10.979
don't ever come
to any of my matches again.

37:12.188 --> 37:15.191
<i>Let's hear it for him, folks.
Brick Armstrong.</i>

37:18.111 --> 37:22.824
All I do is hurt him,
like my dad did to me. I...

37:23.908 --> 37:27.495
I wish I could just wave a magic wand
and be a better dad.

37:27.787 --> 37:29.414
Like a fairy godmother.

37:30.498 --> 37:31.332
Maybe you can.

37:33.334 --> 37:34.544
Get baptized with me tomorrow.

37:35.628 --> 37:38.047
Pastor Mike says it's a new beginning,
a fresh start.

37:38.131 --> 37:40.133
Look. I'd love to believe

37:40.216 --> 37:42.719
that a dip in a kiddie pool
will wash away all my sins

37:42.802 --> 37:46.931
and save my marriage
and improve my relationship with Brick,

37:47.015 --> 37:51.019
but it seems like kind of a lofty
expectation, don't you think?

37:53.313 --> 37:54.647
What do you have to lose?

37:56.232 --> 37:59.944
<i>She had already saved me once
when I was going to end it all.</i>

38:00.195 --> 38:01.738
<i>Maybe she could do it again.</i>

38:02.655 --> 38:04.032
A double dunk.

38:04.741 --> 38:07.494
Well, I like it.
That is, if you're both ready.

38:11.289 --> 38:12.248
Bob.

38:15.919 --> 38:18.963
Mm. So much longing.

38:19.047 --> 38:22.300
Yeah, to fix things with my son.
I really screwed that up.

38:22.383 --> 38:23.802
It's more than that.

38:25.053 --> 38:27.972
You have a God-sized hole.

38:29.724 --> 38:31.768
I don't know what that means.

38:31.851 --> 38:35.647
It means nothing
will ever be enough to fill you up.

38:36.397 --> 38:38.817
Nothing, except the Holy Spirit.

38:41.486 --> 38:44.447
Okay. Am I good to go or what?

38:45.073 --> 38:46.074
You are.

38:46.699 --> 38:49.619
And Bob, whatever it is
you're yearning for,

38:50.119 --> 38:51.371
God will provide.

38:54.499 --> 38:55.500
Patty.

39:01.589 --> 39:03.550
What? What's wrong?

39:04.175 --> 39:05.260
That's a lot going on there.

39:05.927 --> 39:08.137
- You need this more than I thought.
- I know.

39:08.596 --> 39:10.515
I'm starting to wonder
if I'm terminally selfish.

39:10.598 --> 39:12.433
Patty... Shh! Of course you're not.

39:12.517 --> 39:14.561
Hold on, Bob. Patty, what do you mean?

39:15.103 --> 39:16.896
My best friend told me
she was in love with me.

39:16.980 --> 39:19.899
- I could have told you that.
- And I said all of the wrong things.

39:19.983 --> 39:22.485
All I can think about
is getting what I want.

39:22.569 --> 39:24.904
I think even this selfless thing
that I did was all about me.

39:24.988 --> 39:27.156
Patty, stop! We need to get you baptized.

39:27.240 --> 39:29.868
We really do. She really needs this.

39:32.287 --> 39:33.788
What if it doesn't work?

39:34.205 --> 39:37.417
Have you ever had someone
who couldn't be saved?

39:37.500 --> 39:38.626
No.

39:40.169 --> 39:41.004
Not yet.

39:42.422 --> 39:43.715
We'll start in a few minutes.

39:46.968 --> 39:48.469
- Hi.
- Pastor Mike.

39:48.553 --> 39:51.222
- Oh, hi.
- I found something. In my journal.

39:51.306 --> 39:52.307
Okay.

39:53.683 --> 39:56.769
It's a list of all the guys I slept with.

39:56.853 --> 39:58.313
From when I was 17.

39:58.396 --> 40:00.982
Wow. Wow! You were busy.

40:01.190 --> 40:03.318
Kinda thought of it as a badge of honor.

40:03.693 --> 40:05.069
But I was only Patty's age.

40:05.153 --> 40:09.365
And the thought of her like this,
I don't want her to turn out like me.

40:10.283 --> 40:11.326
I need your help.

40:12.118 --> 40:14.579
Tomorrow. Today is Patty's day.

40:15.079 --> 40:17.457
Right. Today's not about me.

40:20.835 --> 40:21.711
Oh.

40:28.509 --> 40:29.344
Hey.

40:30.637 --> 40:33.389
I'm sorry for overreacting
to you guys dating.

40:35.099 --> 40:36.100
You are?

40:37.518 --> 40:39.312
Turns out it was for the best.

40:40.647 --> 40:42.982
I like Christian, a lot.

40:44.567 --> 40:46.819
So... friends?

40:49.155 --> 40:50.281
- Friends.
- Friends.

40:50.365 --> 40:51.658
To you guys.

40:56.788 --> 40:57.830
Wow.

40:58.623 --> 40:59.666
That's a relief.

40:59.749 --> 41:01.417
Did you just make up with Patty?

41:01.876 --> 41:04.963
No. I spiked her cider with liquid molly.

41:05.046 --> 41:08.800
When Pastor Mike sees she's high,
she'll be out of Miss Magic Jesus.

41:09.092 --> 41:10.551
Nobody fucks with a Barnard.

41:12.011 --> 41:13.012
Oh my God.

41:14.889 --> 41:16.849
We are sisters.

41:19.018 --> 41:23.398
We are therefore buried into baptism
with Him through death.

41:23.940 --> 41:28.778
Just as Christ was raised from the dead
through the glory of the Father,

41:28.861 --> 41:31.197
we too may live a new life.

41:31.280 --> 41:32.115
Bob.

41:32.198 --> 41:35.952
<i>For the first time in days,
I finally felt peace.</i>

41:40.832 --> 41:43.668
<i>I could already feel
the power of the Spirit.</i>

41:46.587 --> 41:51.509
<i>I felt warm, ecstatic.
Like I was pure love.</i>

41:52.760 --> 41:56.014
<i>It was a truly religious experience.</i>

41:56.389 --> 41:58.683
<i>I almost felt like I was high.</i>

42:00.351 --> 42:02.770
<i>I just knew once I was dunked,</i>

42:03.396 --> 42:09.485
<i>all my selfishness would be gone
and everything was going to be fine.</i>

42:21.748 --> 42:24.584
<i>Hey. Hey!</i>

42:24.959 --> 42:26.252
<i>Down here.</i>

42:26.335 --> 42:29.005
<i>Yeah, it's me, the donut.</i>

42:29.797 --> 42:31.466
<i>I'm talking to you.</i>

42:31.549 --> 42:34.260
<i>Are you God?</i>

42:34.343 --> 42:38.014
<i>No. I'm your hole.
Your God-sized hole.</i>

42:38.097 --> 42:42.852
<i>The reason you're obsessed with food
and boys and Bob.</i>

42:42.935 --> 42:44.812
<i>What do you want?</i>

42:45.021 --> 42:47.190
<i>I want you to fill me up.</i>

42:47.440 --> 42:50.985
<i>Oh, you'll never be satisfied
unless you take what you want.</i>

42:51.069 --> 42:55.698
I thought
I was supposed to be self "less."

42:56.240 --> 42:59.243
<i>Screw selflessness. You only live once.</i>

42:59.327 --> 43:02.330
<i>Don't let that hot bad boy get away.</i>

43:19.555 --> 43:21.557
Patty's high. Look!

43:24.852 --> 43:27.980
Yes! She was moved by the Spirit.

43:28.064 --> 43:29.482
Oh, that's just bullshit.

43:31.150 --> 43:33.152
God damn it. I'm so sorry, all.

43:34.403 --> 43:38.324
<i>I knew exactly what I wanted.
And exactly what I had to do.</i>

43:38.908 --> 43:40.743
We need to break up, sorry.

43:40.827 --> 43:42.703
<i>- Pastor Mike was wrong.</i>
- Hey, babe...

43:43.162 --> 43:44.789
<i>It wasn't time to be selfless...</i>

43:45.164 --> 43:46.999
You. Come with me.

43:47.375 --> 43:49.710
<i>It was time for me
to finally get what I want.</i>

43:53.756 --> 43:57.176
<i>Patty may have been moved
by the Spirit, but I just felt...</i>

43:57.260 --> 43:59.428
<i>Wet.</i>

44:00.304 --> 44:01.597
<i>Nothing had changed.</i>

44:02.890 --> 44:03.975
Hey, buddy.

44:07.019 --> 44:07.854
You okay?

44:09.147 --> 44:10.398
Patty broke up with me.

44:11.899 --> 44:15.444
My first straight blow off and I really...

44:17.238 --> 44:18.197
I really liked her.

44:20.449 --> 44:21.576
I'm sorry...

44:22.076 --> 44:23.536
for making it about me.

44:25.204 --> 44:26.164
Well, I...

44:27.456 --> 44:28.958
I was thinking about the Regina thing.

44:30.251 --> 44:31.586
You were right, Dad...

44:32.962 --> 44:34.172
that was about you.

44:36.048 --> 44:36.924
So...

44:38.676 --> 44:39.510
sorry.

44:47.435 --> 44:48.936
Coach told me you stopped by.

44:50.146 --> 44:52.440
- And that you let Barnard kick your ass.
- Yeah.

44:52.523 --> 44:55.318
- I even put on a body suit.
- It's a singlet.

44:57.778 --> 44:58.613
Thanks, Dad.

45:05.036 --> 45:08.372
<i>Maybe miracles
were possible after all.</i>

45:23.596 --> 45:27.475
<i>It was finally my time
to get what I wanted.</i>

45:28.476 --> 45:32.188
Wait. I don't have protection.
We don't want any surprises.

45:32.939 --> 45:33.981
Seriously?

45:34.065 --> 45:37.401
Relax. There's other stuff we can do.

45:39.111 --> 45:42.240
I'm gonna do something nice for you.

45:50.706 --> 45:51.707
Oh, God.

